Gold Fields Chief Executive Nick Holland said on Thursday he was not considering resigning after South Africa’s mines minister Gwede Mantashe blamed “poor management” for planned job cuts at its South Deep mine. Mining minister Gwede Mantashe said Gold Fields’ plans to slash jobs at South Deep to reduce costs is taking the “easy way out” and avoids tackling the real issue of poor management. Read: Gold Fields suffering under poor management – Mantashe Asked if he planned to step down, Holland told Reuters: “No.”